added.title: Shrimps and Prime Rib
added.description: The Titans try to remember how to be superheroes in order to stop The Brain.

added.title: TV Knight
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon check in on various happenings around Jump City.

added.title: TV Knight 2
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon have a slumber party and watch their favorite TV shows.

added.title: Thanksgetting
added.description: It's Thanksgiving but the Titans are sick of the normal traditions so they create their own.

added.title: TV Knight 3
added.description: Batman is more interested in watching TV than participating in his birthday party.

added.title: Croissant
added.description: A giant cocoon mysteriously appears in the Titans' living room, and no one can find Beast Boy.

added.title: Black Friday
added.description: Starfire is visited by three ghosts and shown the true meaning of Black Friday.

added.title: Vegetables
added.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Pie Bros
added.description: Beast Boy has to get a job at a pie shop to earn enough money to buy Cyborg a birthday gift, only his job interferes with being able to attend the actual party.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: Buddy's Book
added.description: Steven and Connie take a trip to the library and discover a long forgotten book.

added.title: Doug Out
added.description: Steven and Connie join Connie's father on a stake out.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: Alone at Sea
added.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

added.title: Crack the Whip
added.description: Amethyst is left in charge of Steven and Connie, and there will be no training while she's around!

added.title: Beta
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit some friends in the country but Amethyst isn't being herself.

added.title: Back to the Moon
added.description: Steven and the Gems revisit the Moon Base.

added.title: Bubbled
added.description: Steven gets marooned in his bubble.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: Bubble Buddies
added.description: Steven looks like a hero when he forms a magic crystal bubble around himself to protect a girl he likes from danger, but then panics when he can't figure out how to turn the bubble off!

added.title: An Indirect Kiss
added.description: When Amethyst cracks her gemstone, Steven and the Crystal Gems go on a mission to heal her.

added.title: Fusion Cuisine
added.description: In an effort to win over Connie's parents, Steven convinces the Gems to fuse together and pretend to be his mother.

added.title: Alone Together
added.description: The Gems try to teach Steven to use his fusion powers.

added.title: The Candidate
added.description: When their parents all go to a charity gala at the school, the kids are locked in a classroom with a VHS tape. However, when the room starts to heat up, they need a leader to get them out of the situation and have to choose between Anais, a qualified but unpopular candidate or Gumball, a charismatic candidate with absolutely no plans.

added.title: The Anybody
added.description: Gumball wants Clayton to sit his detention for him, so he convinces him it's way more exciting to be take the shapes of other people.  However, Clayton begins imitating people all over town and causing mayhem. Gumball and Darwin have to convince him that the most exciting person to be is himself.

added.title: The Neighbor
added.description: When their neighbor tries to bring over a package for them, Gumball and Darwin realize they have never learned his name, and it's way too late to ask. They try everything to figure out what it is, but when they do they find out there are bigger secrets to learn about their neighbor than just his name...

added.title: The Shippening
added.description: When people that barely know each other start falling in love, Gumball thinks he knows who's behind it. He rushes to Sarah's house and finds her writing in a magic notebook that turns everything in it into reality. When everything in Elmore gets crazier and crazier there's only one thing for it: they have to write their way out.

added.title: The Brain
added.description: Anais has been facepalming every time her family does something stupid, which has led to a serious medical condition. In fact, if she facepalms just one more time she could do her brain irreparable damage, so the Wattersons have to get through the week without doing anything idiotic.

added.title: The Sale
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are devastated to learn that Mr. Robinson, their favorite person in the world, is selling his house and leaving town. When they realize that making some final happy memories with Mr. Robinson is not enough for them, they decide to stop him leaving by sabotaging the sale.

added.title: The Coach
added.description: The new coach at Elmore High stands up to Jamie. The new Coach witnesses Jamie bullying the other kids at lunch and steps in. Jamie is made to apologise, much to the amazement of the other kids. Gumball and Darwin worry about Jamie seeking revenge, especially when they see him sneaking into the back of Coach's car. They use their newly acquired gym skills to save the Coach from being bullied.

added.title: The Countdown
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are running late for school but need to arrive in time to avoid expulsion. Gumball and Darwin hit snooze too many times on their alarm clock and miss the school-bus. Miss Simian has threatened to expel them if they don't get to school on time. A mysterious clock appears showing exactly how long they have to get to school. When it looks like they aren't going to make it in time, they stop the clock which effects the space/time continuum.

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: The Colossus
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that it isn't wise to upset Hector, Elmore's resident Giant.

added.title: The Apology
added.description: For once in his life Gumball is the one who's owed an apology...from Ms Simian!

added.title: The Authority
added.description: Granny JoJo's overprotective behavior puts the Wattersons in danger...from themselves.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

added.title: The Ape
added.description: Ms Simian sets out to "befriend" Gumball in order to win a Favourite Teacher Award.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Gumball experiences an impossibly unfortunate chain of events.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: #Frenemies Part 1
added.description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

added.title: #Frenemies Part 2
added.description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

added.title: Whatever Happened to... Rippy Roo?
added.description: Rippy Roo visits the plaza.

added.title: Let's Meet Sonic
added.description: When world class hero SONIC THE HEDGEHOG visits the plaza, he teams up with KO to save the day.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: You're a Good Friend, KO
added.description: KO brings Dendy along for a hero mission in order to cheer her up.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: Dendy's Power
added.description: Dendy and KO discover a fun and exciting new POW Card exploit.

added.title: Crossover Nexus
added.description: When KO finds himself trapped inside an mysterious place, he encounters other Cartoon Network Heroes and they band together to escape.

added.title: Super Black Friday
added.description: After being forced to work on a holiday, KO, Rad and Enid take a stand.

added.title: A Hero's Fate
added.description: When a long lost hero stumbles into Gar's, KO agrees to help him complete his years long quest.

added.title: KO's Video Channel
added.description: Enid and Rad discover that KO has a video channel.

added.title: Back in Red Action
added.description: Enid teams up with Red Action to take on a menace from the future.

added.title: Lad & Logic
added.description: KO learns the story of how Mr. Logic came to the plaza.

added.title: Action News
added.description: Dynamite Watkins has to go extreme lengths breaking a new story.

added.title: Hope This Flies
added.description: Rad attempts to upgrade his van and make it fly.

added.title: Breezy
added.description: With a friendly bee named "Breezy" as his wingman, Finn decides to get back into the dating game.

added.title: Everything's Jake
added.description: Jake finds himself transported to a world both alien and familiar.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: The Thanksgiving Special
added.description: The park guys need to get Thanksgiving dinner for their families to save Thanksgiving.

added.title: Burning Low
added.description: Finn starts spending a lot of time with Flame Princess...is Princess Bubblegum jealous?

added.title: BMO Noire
added.description: When Finn thinks he's lost a sock, B-Mo is covertly on the case.

added.title: The Phone Call
added.description: A threatening phone call from a stranger causes the gang to panic.

added.title: Stick Hockey
added.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.

added.title: Midnight Madness
added.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Except for Cooper
added.description: A young boy must learn to eat his spinach in order to save Uncle Grandpa and the others from a rowdy gang of evil vegetables.

added.title: Eggscellent
added.description: Mordecai wants to win a hat for Rigby.

added.title: Sugar Rush
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up the donuts for the morning meeting.

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: Secret Science Part 1
added.description: While studying the scraplets Wheeljack is kidnapped by Shockwave who tries to enlist Wheeljack's help.

added.title: Secret Science Part 2
added.description: Wheeljack attempts to break out of the Nemesis while Windblade hunts down Bludgeon to avenge Slipstream.

added.title: A Bunch of Baby Ducks
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby come across a family of ducks living in a fountain at the park and take quite a shine to them.

added.title: The Buttercup Job
added.description: Buttercup joins Jemmica in a quest for adventure, but how far will she go?

added.title: Toy Ploy
added.description: When Mojo kidnaps the girls' favorite snuggle toys, he gets more than he bargained for.

added.title: Bubbles the Blue
added.description: When Bubbles isn't her normal, bubbly self, her sisters don't know how to handle it.

added.title: Man Up 3: The Good, the Bad, and the Manly
added.description: After Bubbles gets blasted with Man Boy's beard ray, she wreaks havoc in the most manly and adorable way possible.

added.title: Aliver
added.description: The Girls compete for the title of World's Greatest Superheroes!

added.title: Free Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby throw Skips a surprise birthday party in order to get free cake.

added.title: #LaCubetaDeBurritos
added.description: A Babs le encanta su trabajo en el restaurante de comida rápida "La Cubeta de Burritos" , pero a su jefe, que está harto de que ella siempre llegue tarde y de su enorme dispersión, le encantaría encontrar cualquier excusa para despedirla. Cuando se produce un robo a un banco que está enfrente de su trabajo, Babs no puede decidir si encarnar su papel de superheroína o el de empleada obediente de La Cubeta. Pero ¿será capaz de salvar a todos y conservar su empleo justo a tiempo?
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #ConoceAGuepardo
added.description: Barbara Minerva está super celosa de la "pequeña señorita perfecta" Diana Prince. Pero cuando usa un antiguo artefacto de la colección de su padre para lanzar una maldición contra Diana, la maldición se vuelve en su contra.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Dungeon
added.description: Finn tries to conquer a dungeon without Jake's help.

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
added.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

added.title: Chimney
added.description: While playing in the woods the boys befriend a wild dog, bring it home and name it Chimney. When the boys find themselves trapped in a well, the new pup is their only hope for escape.

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: Bureaucrophobia
added.description: Teri Gargantuan is in trouble and her spider kids hire the Warriors to save their mom from a mad mercenary spider hunter.

added.title: Hunting for Scavengers
added.description: When an impish weather gnome sends the Warriors and friends on a competitive quest, the drive to win threatens the group's fight against a conjured monster.

added.title: Unconventional Dolphinism
added.description: Since Prohyas is taking Dolphin Magisword to the Dolphin Convention, Vambre asks Witchy Simone to join her on a search for the Narwhal Magisword, angering a deadly Sealdebeast guard that lures dolphins away from the convention in the process.

added.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
added.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

added.title: Bad Heir Day
added.description: Princess Zange's Autostyle Magisword is stolen and it's up to the Warriors to retrieve it so their royal leader can face her subjects without bad hair.

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Wasteland
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa neglects his garbage duties, he embarks on a quest to save his friends from the overflowing pile of trash.

added.title: Cough It Up
added.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
added.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

added.title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
added.description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
added.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

added.title: Worm Bin
added.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: Clarence's Millions
added.description: When Clarence realizes the classroom "buddy star" system is leaving some kids behind, he creates his own form of currency called "Clarence Dollars." The new reward system promptly turns the entire school upside down.

added.title: Honk
added.description: Seeking to improve his communication skills, Clarence turns to a squeeze horn. It's really annoying.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Zoo
added.description: Clarence and Belson make a true odd couple when they're paired up during a field trip to the zoo and find themselves locked inside after hours.

added.title: Blossom3
added.description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

added.title: Small World: Abra-Disaster Part 1
added.description: After defeating Mojo for the umpteenth time, the Powerpuff Girls are confident they are unstoppable.

added.title: Small World: Stone Cold Spider Part 2
added.description: With Townsville in peril, the girls are sent to the arctic on a dangerous mission to find the key to saving the day.

added.title: Small World: Maze Daze Part 3
added.description: The girls must enter a cursed jungle temple to obtain the last Heart Stone.

added.title: Small World: Heart to Heartstone Part 4
added.description: In the stunning conclusion, the girls learn Lester has one more trick up his sleeve.

added.title: Criss Cross Crisis
added.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

added.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
added.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Bubbles of the Opera
added.description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: Electric Buttercup
added.description: Buttercup gets more than she bargained for when she makes a deal with a cool '80s metalhead to get a sweet new guitar.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down 'N Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Three Girls and a Monster/Monkey See, Doggy Two
added.description: Three Girls and a Monster: The girls are once again in a furious battle with a ferocious monster. But Blossom and Buttercup can't agree on how to fight the beast and Bubbles just wants everyone to get along./Monkey See, Doggy Two: Mojo has discovered a fatal flaw in his brilliant plan and decides to reenact it step-by-step. The girls think they're experiencing deja vu but it's really just Mojo working his maniacal mischief.

added.title: I See a Funny Cartoon in Your Future/Octi-Gone
added.description: I See a Funny Cartoon In Your Future: The girls have the rare task of fighting a medium who is committing petty thefts./Octi-gone: When Bubbles finds a single leg of Octi's, she sets out to find out who took her toy and what they want from her.

added.title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
added.description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
added.description: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

added.title: Agent of Destruction
added.description: DeBizz helps the Warriors become more famous as their agent, but Vambre returns to adventuring while Prohyas gets caught up in the DeBizz fame trap.

added.title: Dunkadellic
added.description: After suffering trauma from being the dunk-ee in a dunking booth, Prohyas has trouble getting through the dunk based traps in Man Fish's lair.

added.title: Warts and All
added.description: Witchy Simone accidentally turns Vambre into a frog and Prohyas and Witchy try to change her back.

added.title: Too Commercial
added.description: The Warriors go advertising crazy; Grup tries to stop them for their own good!

added.title: Like Water for Bimm
added.description: Vambre helps to get Bimm over her mission crippling fear of water.

added.title: The Pecking Order
added.description: Professor Cyrus hires the Warriors to take Frank-Paul through a treacherous mountain pass so he can molt at the top of Mt. Chickicken.

added.title: Manlier Fish the Fishlier Man
added.description: With the help of a conch shell genie, Man Fish upgrades himself in various ways to defeat the Warriors.

added.title: Fionna and Cake and Fionna
added.description: An unexpected critic shows up at Ice King's latest Fionna and Cake book reading.

added.title: All Your Fault
added.description: Princess Bubblegum sends Finn and Jake to investigate a message of distress from the Earls of Lemongrab.

added.title: Bad Little Boy
added.description: The princesses are sick and tired of Ice King's crazy Fionna & Cake stories, so Marceline stops by the Ice Kingdom to show him how it's done.

added.title: BMO Lost
added.description: BMO gets snatched away by a giant eagle and must find his way home.

added.title: Be More
added.description: Finn and Jake disguise themselves as MOs in order to infiltrate the MO factory in hopes of saving BMO from malfunctioning.

added.title: Betty
added.description: In Wizard City, a magic spell backfires and turns Ice King back into Simon. Now with Finn, Jake and Marceline's help, Simon finds a way to bring his beloved Betty back. Finally reunited with the love of his life, everything is great! There's just one catch...without his magic crown, Simon will die.

added.title: Belly of the Beast

added.title: Chili Cook-Off

added.title: Rigby in the Sky with Burrito

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe

added.title: Divided We Stand
added.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
added.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

added.title: Rook Tales
